application_type_full: Tree works: Trees in conservation areas/subject to TPOs
description: Works to various trees covered by LBE ORDER NO 272 (2001):A) 1x smoke bush (G1): cut back growth to boundary by 2m;1x pissard plum (G2): cut back growth from fence by 2m; group of 3 Prunus (G42): cut back to boundary by 2m; 1x smoke bush (G47): cut back to boundary by 2m; 1x willow (T3): fell and replace with cherry; 1x ash (T4) & 1x mountain ash (T8): de-compact soil around bases of trees; 1x mountain ash (T7): fell and replace with Prunus; 1x lime (T9): raise low canopy to 3m, remove deadwood and epicormic growth; 1x small-leafed lime (T10): remove epicormic growth; 1x lime (T11): raise low canopy to 3m and remove epicormic growth; 1x small-leafed lime (T12): raise low canopy to 2.5m and remove epicormic growth; 1x silver lime (T13): remove epicormic growth; 1x lime (T15): raise low canopy to 3m; 3x limes (T14,T16,T17): raise low canopies to 3m and remove epicormic growth; 1x lime (T20): fell to ground level and apply systemic herbicide to stump; 1x small-leafed lime (T21): remove epicormic growth; 1x lime (T22): re-pollard by 3m; 1x lime (T23): raise low canopy to 4m; 1x ash (T25): remove tree grille and de-compact soil; 1x oak (T27) and 3x limes (T28,T29,T30): raise low canopies to 3m; 1x lime (T32) and 1x ash (T33): raise low canopies to 3m and remove deadwood; 2x London planes (T35,T36,T39,T40): sever ivy and remove deadwood; 1x ash (T45): fell and replace with Prunus, 3x Prunus kanzans (T48,T49,T50): raise low canopies to 3m.B) 1x lime (T31): pollard to 5m.
site_name: Southbury Leisure Park192 Southbury RoadEnfieldEN1 1YP
decision_conditions: Replacement Trees for T3, T7 and T45
